---
title: Caramelized Apple Cheddar Melts with a Honey Dijon Arugula Salad
description: Sure, a classic white bread and American cheese melt hits the spot every now and then—but try one bite of this sweet and savory sandwich, and you just might want to add it to your weeknight repertoire. Sourdough bread slices are swiped with Dijon mustard, then layered with white and yellow cheddar and a caramelized apple filling. They’re griddled in butter until perfectly golden brown and melty and paired with arugula, dried cranberries, and sunflower seeds tossed in a tangy Honey Dijon Dressing.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/caramelized-apple-cheddar-melts-4434d104.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/caramelized-apple-cheddar-melts-5f69048d69aa6f3f5e056c1b-eab49eae.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 860 kcal
  fat: 48 g
  saturated fat: 21 g
  carbohydrates: 85 g
  sugar: 27 g
  protein: 22 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 1130 mg
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/caramelized-apple-cheddar-melts-5f69048d69aa6f3f5e056c1b
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce.

Halve, core, and finely dice @apple{1}(halved, cored, and finely diced). Strip @thyme{1/4%ounce}(minced) leaves from stems; mince leaves until you have 2 tsp.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add apple; cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add @sugar{1/2%teaspoon}, minced thyme, and 1 TBSP water. Cook, stirring, until apple is caramelized and jammy, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Turn off heat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}; transfer to a #small bowl{}.

Place @sourdough bread{4%slices} on a clean work surface. Spread half the slices with @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoons}, then top with @white cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}, caramelized apple, and @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}. Place remaining bread slices on top to create sandwiches.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in pan used for apple over medium heat. Add sandwiches and cook until golden brown on first side, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Remove sandwiches; add another @butter{1%tablespoon} to pan. Once butter has melted, return sandwiches to pan and cook on second side until bread is golden brown and cheese has melted, ~{4-5%minutes} more.

While sandwiches cook, add @arugula{2%ounce} to a large bowl along with @dried cranberries{1.16%ounce} and @sunflower seeds{1/2%ounce}; toss with as much @Honey Dijon Dressing{1.5%ounce} as you like. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Halve melts on a diagonal.

Divide salad and melts between plates. Serve with any remaining Honey Dijon Dressing on the side for dipping.

> Sure, a classic white bread and American cheese melt hits the spot every now and then—but try one bite of this sweet and savory sandwich, and you just might want to add it to your weeknight repertoire.